<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <head>
        <link href="" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Text </span>Enter a caption (or title) for the table. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare-Online-Only">For details on how to use autonumbering on a table caption, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Tutorials/Tables-Tutorial/Tables-Tutorial.htm">Tables Tutorial</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li>
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Side </span>Click in this field and select to place the caption either above or below the table.</p>
                <div class="note" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">
                    <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">Due to an issue with Internet Explorer, selecting <span class="Emphasis">Below table</span> may place the caption <i>above</i> the table in outputs based on Internet Explorer.</p>
                </div>
                <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../Styles/Note-Rounded-Table-Borders-Captions.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare" />
            </li>
            <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Tables-Guide" />
            <li>
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Repeat&#160;</span>If you want captions to repeat on tables that span multiple pages in print-based output, select <span class="Emphasis">Repeat</span> from this field. </p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl/Tables/Table-Caption-Repeat-Continuation1.png" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
                <div class="note" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">
                    <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can also edit this option in the regular stylesheet using the <span class="Emphasis">mc-caption-repeat</span> property. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Styles/Main-Activities/Editing-Styles.htm">Editing Styles</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                    <p>In addition, you can edit table cell properties in the regular stylesheet. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Tables/Main-Activities/Editing-Table-Cell-Properties.htm">Editing Table Cell Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Tables-Guide" />
            <li>
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Continuation </span>In this field, you can enter continuation text to the end of captions that repeat (other than the caption appearing on the first page where a table occurs). Typically this text would be something like "(continued)."</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl/Tables/Table-Caption-Repeat-Continuation2.png" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
                <div class="note" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">
                    <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #242729;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can also edit this option in the regular stylesheet using the <span class="Emphasis">mc-caption-continuation</span> property. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Styles/Main-Activities/Editing-Styles.htm">Editing Styles</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                    <p>In addition, you can edit table cell properties in the regular stylesheet. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Tables/Main-Activities/Editing-Table-Cell-Properties.htm">Editing Table Cell Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>